## LIVE production path (docker-fleet AX41 — 116.202.113.146)

- **Trigger**: push to `main`
- **Pipeline**: GHA `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml` → build → push to `ghcr.io/digitalsoftdistribution/<repo>:main` → SSH-deploy
- **Host**: `/srv/<app>/{docker-compose.yml,.env}` deploys as `deploy` user
- **SSL**: Cloudflare Tunnel `docker-fleet` (id `64b737b9-...`) terminates TLS at edge
- **DNS**: `<app>.com` CNAME → `64b737b9-...cfargotunnel.com` (proxied)
- **In Coolify on old AX41**: `is_auto_deploy_enabled = false`

## Preview / branch / PR path (old AX41 — 95.217.117.169)

- **Trigger**: any non-main branch push + PR open/sync (Coolify GH App webhook)
- **Pipeline**: Coolify v4 at `new-coolify.softblaze.net`
- **Coolify-Traefik bound to 127.0.0.1:8180/8543** (does not fight CyberPanel/OLS for 80/443)
- **SSL**: CF Tunnel `softblaze-preview-wildcard` routes `*.apps.softblaze.net` → `localhost:8180`
- **For preview-only apps**: `is_auto_deploy_enabled = true` (main also lands here)
- **For LIVE prod apps**: `is_auto_deploy_enabled = false`, but `preview_deployments_enabled = true` (PRs only)

## Anti-patterns — DO NOT

- ❌ Enable Coolify auto_deploy on a LIVE prod app (races GHA — duplicate builds)
- ❌ Add `<app>.com` to Coolify domains (Coolify only handles `.apps.softblaze.net`)
- ❌ Add Let's Encrypt / ACME on origin — CF terminates TLS at the edge
- ❌ Route `<app>.com` through old AX41 (containers were stopped 2026-06-03 — ports 3212/3213 freed)

## Cursor + Claude agents — when to use which path

| Situation | Where to deploy |
|---|---|
| Adding new LIVE site with public domain | docker-fleet (set up `/srv/<app>` + GHA workflow + tunnel ingress + CNAME) |
| Internal tool, only need preview URL | Coolify only (add app via API, `is_auto_deploy_enabled = true`) |
| Adding feature flag / branch deploy | Coolify auto-creates on PR open |
| Hotfix to prod | push to main of LIVE app → GHA deploys (skip Coolify) |
| Long-running staging of a feature | Coolify branch deploy (separate Coolify app pointing at that branch) |

## Build file convention (added 2026-06-03)

**Each LIVE-prod repo can have TWO build paths** (used by different consumers):

| File | Used by | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Dockerfile` (or absent — Coolify uses nixpacks) | Coolify previews on old AX41 | Fast preview build per PR; nixpacks auto-detect OR explicit Dockerfile if needed |
| `Dockerfile.prod` | GHA `deploy-prod.yml` → docker-fleet | Production-optimized build for live deploys |

For monorepo repos (e.g. tracklayer), `Dockerfile.prod` should:
- Use the right pnpm workspace filter (e.g. `pnpm --filter @org/web build`)
- Output the production-ready container (Next.js standalone, etc.)
- Be self-contained (no dev deps, multi-stage, slim runtime)

The GHA workflow `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml` references `file: Dockerfile.prod` explicitly via `docker/build-push-action`. If the file doesn't exist, the build fails. **That's a feature** — it prevents accidentally deploying preview-quality builds to prod.
